metadata.name: In the Edge #1
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.

metadata.name: unbuilt #127
metadata.description:
This is a journey through architecture that never existed.

Inspired by the grammatical rules behind French sacral architecture of the Middle Ages, this generative tool is meant for creating a collection of 256 plans of fictional buildings. Each plan is a unique variation on semantic relations between architectural elements: from a regular composition resembling existing churches to a dynamic aggregation of vaults, columns and chevets. But always following the same set of rules extracted from multiple examples of gothic cathedrals.

Every church has its place and time in which it could have been built in an alternative series of historical events.

This artistic tribute to the research of Stiny and Mitchell about Palladian architecture or Duarte's work about Siza takes the topic of formalizing architectural language onto a lighthearted level by moving it to a slightly imaginary world.

To zoom, press a mouse button when over the image or touch the screen. To pan, keep the mouse pressed and move it around.

metadata.name: FAT Christmas #745
metadata.description:
“FAT Christmas” 由三位台灣創作者主導，並且與另外幾位創作者共創部件。包含發行過 Moonlight Impression 的 mido、影像創作者 Graphyni、熱衷 AI 生成的 Fagem。
你可以在這個生成器中獲取 Chang Ming Yao 的 Aka’s Ape 或由 Chi.L 繪製的 AKAZOO Cat，甚至是 roupin_art 的 Dino Ali。
並祝福所有 Tezos 的創作者與藏家，接下來一年能充滿希望。

我們竭盡所能的補充多樣性，確保每次鑄造都是明確且獨特的結果。
在30多種的背景中，包含由創作者提供的特殊款式，如果你足夠幸運，將有機會獲得美麗且獨特的角色 。

角色方面：
Aka’s Ape 包含 8 種 character、8 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、3 種 personality。
Aka Zoo Cat 包含 7 種 character、10 種 eyes、7 種 mouth、5 種  personality。
Dino Ali 包含 26 種 character、5 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、6 種 personality。
所有角色共享超過 20 款頭飾、9 款服裝、10 種服裝印花。
角色前方桌面的三個位置，亦各自包含 10 種以上的配件。

由衷的希望各位都能玩得開心。
祝大家聖誕快樂，新年快樂。

“FAT Christmas” is a collabration of three creators from Taiwan, with parts contributed by creators including mido's “Moonlight Impression”, video creator Graphyni and generative AI enthusiast Fagem.
You can get Aka’s Ape by Chang Ming Yao, AKAZOO  Cat by Chi.L and Dino Ali by roupin_art from the generator.
Blessing to all Tezos creators and collectors, filled with hope in the coming year.

Diversity is replenished in our best effort to ensure apparent and unique results in every mint.
Among over 30 different backgrounds, including special design provided by the creators, you will have a chance to get a gorgeous and unique character if you are lucky enough.

About the characters:
Aka’s Ape includes 8 types of character, 8 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 3 types of personality.
Aka Zoo Cat includes 7 types of character, 10 types of eyes, 7 types of mouth and 5 types of personality.
Dino Ali includes 26 types of character, 5 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 6 types of personality.
All characters share over 20 headwears, 9 clothes and 10 clothes patterns.
Over 10 decorations will be assigned to 3 positions on the table in front of the character.

Sincerely hope everyone can have fun.
And wishing you all a Merry Christmas and a happy new year.

metadata.name: Computing memory #119
metadata.description:
This creation takes Penghu, Taiwan, my hometown as the theme, and uses the style of expired films to reconstruct the scene in my memory.
During the creative process, I think about how "mechanism" and "choice" affect the scene in my memory, I also asked myself in the process of creation, did I discover the appearance left in my memory after this work or was it the appearance I hoped to see?

2023 shengkai

metadata.name: Fragmented triacontahedron with iPhone 5s #6
metadata.description:
Title: Fragmented rhombic triacontahedron with model iPhone 5s
Media: Interactive WebGL, resolution variable

A randomized composition of digital artifacts. Scans of a plaster sculpture that has been deliberately shattered. A deconstructed 3d model of an iPhone 5s. Original photography, textures, screen captures and found images. Stream of consciousness text.

* Mouse to orbit. Scroll wheel to zoom.

metadata.name: Electric Hope #338
metadata.description:
Perceived as fabric of dark and vivid thoughts, hope is always there. Sparse layers of squares form an intricate colorful lattice reflecting mixed feelings of hopelessness and hopefulness, doubt and optimism.

Press S to save. To download in custom size (ex. 2000px width), add &size=2000 to url, reload and press S.

Inspired by CMYK halftone printing patterns

Made with p5js especially for #fxhashturnsone event. 50% of primary sales will be donated to Processing Foundation

metadata.name: Coronado #390
metadata.description:
This series is about the beauty and charm of imperfection, chaos amidst order, and letting go. It's about knowing that however much control we think we may have, things can all fall apart or burst into something unexpectedly wonderful at any moment, even without our hands tightly on the reigns.

Please see fxtext article linked from main project page for more background on the project and rendering notes.

Some key commands in live mode:

G : Toggle grain
S : Save current resolution
1 : 4000x5000
2 : 6000x7500
3 : 8000x10000
4 : 10000x12500
5 : 12000x15000
6 : 14000x17500
(1-6 work best on Chrome)
(rendering takes longer as resolution increases)

metadata.name: Univercell #89
metadata.description:
⚗🦠🌌✨

The center of a digital, quantified space emits 2 560 000 particles through a sequence of expansions, contractions and perturbations. 🌌

Once formed, the evolution of the Univercell can be observed through a series of animations in the manner of a documentary. 🎥

Each Univercell is a unique random and deterministic composition. 🔮

(Click ‘open’ and go fullscreen for best experience !)

🎄🌟🪐🌈☀




-----
* Mint preview *

Minter will get a 1920x1920 PNG bitmap and an infinite animation.

-----
* Technics *

This experience is designed to be executed on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on 16/9 screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 → 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

The physics algorithms take around 20 seconds to generate one Univercell. During generation, a progress indication in percentage is displayed.

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL
- Unique generative and determinist animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Unlimited duration (no loop) / 6 documentary animations
- 20 seconds internal algorithm variations

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view frame (same ratio as window, max 1920x1080)

⚗ Empiric mode (empiric=on / see URL modifiers below)
Wheel/pinch : zoom in/out to observe the Univercell on different scales
Right click + drag : move the observation area
Keyboard "R" : enable automatic rotation of view

-----
* URL modifiers *

"&empiric=on"
Turn off animations and display a Univercell that can be manually explored.

"&demo=on"
Reduce the cinematics duration to 5 seconds. Allows faster cycling through documentary phases.

"&random=on"
Randomize documentary sequences order.


-----
@HAL09999 – December 21st, 2022

metadata.name: Nanopanorama #189
metadata.description:
Distorted noise with weird textures and funky shapes rendered using my rayhatcher algorithm.

4671 characters of pure Javascript, no libraries.

Some options can be changed via the URL:

&lw=.25 : The linewidth in millimetres.
&d=.4 : Line density (multiplier to linewidth).
&h=235 : Page height in millimetres. The aspect ratio is 16:9, for a width of 420mm, suitable for A3 plotting.
&bg=1 : Set to 0 to remove background rectangle (recommended for plotting).

When plotting, it is recommended to use a path reordering / optimizing tool such as axicli or vpype to greatly reduce the plotting time.

metadata.name: codeTurning 1: Dotting #47
metadata.description:
The codeTurning project aims to reflect my journey from traditional tools to code, in which any day I learn a new skill.
Join me towards something new for me. Something different from the previous. 
Sometimes we will stand on the shoulders of giants.
 
Let's explore and see how far we get.
 
Lesson 1: Dotting
 
This is my first step.
The dotting series explores the technique of painting with dots-of-paint placed pseudo-randomly on the canvas.
 
------------
Thanks to Dario, Fernando, Alejandro, Piter, Diego, Manuel and Anthony for their support, especially for helping me to set up my project in the fxhash infrastructure.
